## Test on t + 1

# use the model trainined in year t to predict io of year t + 1
years <- (2000:2009)
pred.by.year <- data.frame(matrix(NA,nrow=1369, ncol = 0))
for (i in years){
  t_plus_1 <- i +1
  pred <- predict(fit.year[names(fit.year)==i], total[total$year==t_plus_1,])
  pred <- as.data.frame(pred)
  rownames(pred) <- c()
  pred.by.year <- cbind(pred.by.year, pred)
}
#change column names to match with total
names(pred.by.year) <- 2001:2010
# wide to long
pred.by.year <- gather(pred.by.year,key = year,value = predictions,1:10)
# drop 2000 and select variables form total
total.no2000 <- total %>% filter(year!=2000) %>% dplyr::select(id, year, io)
# column bind prediction and data  
pred.by.year <- cbind(pred.by.year, total.no2000)
# pred.by.year to list by year
pred.by.year.list <- split(pred.by.year, pred.by.year$year)
# calculate metrics for every year
rf.all.caret.year.metrics <- lapply(pred.by.year.list, function(x) postResample(pred = x$predictions,
                                                                     obs = x$io))
rf.all.caret.year.metrics %>% as.data.frame() %>%
  round(2) %>%
  kable()

Model with caret(): train on year t and t + 1 with CV, report accuracy, test on t + 2 (unseen data)

## Train on t

# split the data by year into a list
#by.year <- split(total, total$year)

# CV
tc <- trainControl(method = "cv",
                   number = 10,
                   savePredictions = 'final')

# run the model for every 2 years
years <- 2000:2010

for (t in years){
  tplus1 <- t + 1
  set.seed(71)
  model <- train(io ~ hl + dist + gva.orig + gva.dest + central.orig + central.dest,
                 data = total[total$year==t | total$year==tplus1,],
                 trControl = tc,
                 method = "rf", importance = TRUE)
  #paste("model", t + 1, t + 2, sep="_")
  assign(as.character(t + 1), model)
}

# It will create: 2001 (train on 2000-2001) - 2011 (train on 2010)
# I need: 2001 (train on 2000-2001) - 2009 (train on 2008-2009)

# create a list of the above model outputs
fit.year <- mget(ls(pattern = "^20"))

# resamples
fit.year.res <- resamples(fit.year)
summary(fit.year.res)

Model with caret() and Extreme Gradient Boosting: train on year t and t + 1 with CV, report accuracy, test on t + 2 (unseen data)

The hyper parameters are directly taken from this tutorial.

## Train on t

# CV
tc <- trainControl(method = "cv",
                   number = 10,
                   savePredictions = 'final',
                   #allowParallel = TRUE,
                   verboseIter = FALSE,
                   returnData = FALSE)

# https://datascienceplus.com/extreme-gradient-boosting-with-r/
xgbGrid <- expand.grid(nrounds = c(100,200),  # this is n_estimators in the python code above
                       max_depth = c(10, 15, 20, 25),
                       colsample_bytree = seq(0.5, 0.9, length.out = 5),
                       ## The values below are default values in the sklearn-api.
                       eta = 0.1,
                       gamma=0,
                       min_child_weight = 1,
                       subsample = 1
                      )

# run the model for every 2 years
years <- 2000:2010

for (t in years){
  tplus1 <- t + 1
  set.seed(71)
  model <- train(io ~ hl + dist + central.orig + central.dest + gva.orig + gva.dest,
                 data = total[total$year==t | total$year==tplus1,],
                 #data = total[total$year==2000 | total$year==2001,],
                 trControl = tc,
                 tuneGrid = xgbGrid,
                 method = "xgbTree", importance = TRUE)
  #paste("model", t + 1, t + 2, sep="_")
  assign(as.character(t + 1), model)
}
